[{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"HowTo","name":"Vinyl Siding Lights: How to Mount Lights Using a Vinyl Mounting Block","description":" Create a rock-solid base for exterior light fixtures mounted on vinyl or aluminum lap siding, without removing any siding. Vinyl mounting blocks are available for almost any lap and securely hold lights upright.","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.familyhandyman.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/FH06APR_467_05_015_hsp.jpg","height":1200,"width":1200},"supply":[{"@type":"HowToSupply","name":"Cable connector"},{"@type":"HowToSupply","name":"Caulk"},{"@type":"HowToSupply","name":"Exterior screws"},{"@type":"HowToSupply","name":"Vinyl mounting block"},{"@type":"HowToSupply","name":"Wire nuts"}],"tool":[{"@type":"HowToTool","name":"4-in-1 screwdriver"},{"@type":"HowToTool","name":"Cordless drill"},{"@type":"HowToTool","name":"Wire stripper/cutter"}],"step":[{"@type":"HowToStep","url":"https://www.familyhandyman.com/electrical/outdoor-lighting/vinyl-siding-lights-how-to-mount-lights-using-a-vinyl-mounting-block/#step1","name":"Mounting lights on vinyl siding","itemListElement":{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"\r\nVinyl mounting block\r\n\r\n\r\nMounting blocks are available in different sizes and profiles.\r\n\r\nDIY Outdoor Lighting Tips for Beginners\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n"},"Image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.familyhandyman.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Vinyl.jpg","height":"1200","width":"1200"}},{"@type":"HowToStep","url":"https://www.familyhandyman.com/electrical/outdoor-lighting/vinyl-siding-lights-how-to-mount-lights-using-a-vinyl-mounting-block/#step2","name":"","itemListElement":{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"\r\nMounting box with built-in electrical box\r\n\r\n\r\nPush the wire through the cable connecter, then screw the block to the sheathing.For adequate support, you can mount exterior light fixtures to a solid block or base, which you usually install before or during the siding process. However, when retrofitting lights on vinyl or aluminum siding or fixing a sagging fixture it's usually easier to buy special blocks that fit right over the siding (available at home centers).\r\n\r\n14 Outdoor Lighting Trends for 2018\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n"},"Image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.familyhandyman.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/electrical.jpg","height":"1200","width":"1200"}},{"@type":"HowToStep","url":"https://www.familyhandyman.com/electrical/outdoor-lighting/vinyl-siding-lights-how-to-mount-lights-using-a-vinyl-mounting-block/#step3","name":"The mounting blocks are paintable","itemListElement":{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n and available in different sizes and profiles to fit most types of flat and lap vinyl siding styles. You don't have to cut into the siding to mount the block. However, light fixtures must be secured to an electrical box. The block we show here has a built-in electrical box, so you don't need the one in the wall. If you use a block without an electrical box, shift the existing electrical box out so you can mount the fixture to it.\r\n\r\nTo install the kit, insert the cable connector in an opening in the center of the mounting block, then feed in the cable(s) from the back. Set the block into place as shown and screw it to 1/2-in. (minimum) wood sheathing. Or mount it to a stud. Connect the wires, mount the fixture and caulk around the block so it's watertight.\r\n\r\nLow-Voltage Outdoor Lighting\r\n\r\n "},"Image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.familyhandyman.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/shutterstock_751934287-paint.jpg","height":"1200","width":"1200"}}]},{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"BlogPosting","headline":"Vinyl Siding Lights: How to Mount Lights Using a Vinyl Mounting Block","mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.familyhandyman.com/electrical/outdoor-lighting/vinyl-siding-lights-how-to-mount-lights-using-a-vinyl-mounting-block/"},"description":"Mount lights on any type of vinyl or metal siding","datePublished":"2019-03-22T00:00:07Z","dateModified":"2019-03-22T15:04:45Z","author":[{"@type":"Organization","name":"The Family Handyman"}],"image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.familyhandyman.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/FH06APR_467_05_015_hsp.jpg","height":1200,"width":1200},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"The Family Handyman","logo":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.familyhandyman.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/amp_sd_logo.png","width":198,"height":60}},"url":"https://www.familyhandyman.com/electrical/outdoor-lighting/vinyl-siding-lights-how-to-mount-lights-using-a-vinyl-mounting-block/","dateCreated":"2019-03-22T00:00:07Z","articleSection":"Outdoor Lighting","creator":[{"@type":"Organization","name":"The Family Handyman"}],"keywords":""},{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"BreadcrumbList","itemListElement":[{"@type":"ListItem","position":1,"item":{"@id":"https://www.familyhandyman.com/","name":"Home"}},{"@type":"ListItem","position":2,"item":{"@id":"https://www.familyhandyman.com/electrical/","name":"Electrical"}},{"@type":"ListItem","position":3,"item":{"@id":"https://www.familyhandyman.com/electrical/outdoor-lighting/","name":"Outdoor Lighting"}}]}]
